GURAN: The story has problems as period detail, language, atmosphere. logic, and even theology.
\par (1) Overall the entire introductory paragraphs need to be rethought. The dust metaphor breaks down anyway, as they are in the desert, not a Dust Bowl area for the action. Moreover, with the beginning as is, it lacks immediacy.
\par (2) I think a lot of this intro was meant to set up the concept that the dust made zombies, yet really there\rquote s only a vague, easy to misinterpret or miss.
\par (3) Where these folks are from is very important to them, yet no reference until later. Nor to what they 
left behind. A better lead-in might be to simply set up the story and forget the poetics and unsustained metaphor OR sustain the metaphor by locating somewhere other than desert.}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af5 \ltrch\fcs0 \f5\insrsid11670705 
